What is Ingres?

Ingres is one of the world's earliest Relational Database Management Systems (RDBMS).

It was developed at the University of California, Berkeley in the early 1970s.

What does "Ingres" mean?

Ingres is short for:

INteractive GRaphics and REtrieval System

Breaking it down:
----------------

IN   → Interactive
GR   → Graphics
RES  → Retrieval System

↓

INGRES

===
Meaning:

Interactive → Users can interact directly with the database.
Graphics → The original project was related to interactive graphics applications.
Retrieval System → Used to retrieve (search and access) stored data.

