What is Ingres?

Answer:

Ingres is an early Relational Database Management System (RDBMS) developed at the University of California, Berkeley. 
Its name is an abbreviation of INteractive GRaphics and REtrieval System. 
It inspired the development of POSTGRES, which later evolved into PostgreSQL.

